  "texts": [
    "In contrast, Tran et al. [90] observed little effect on workability at lower replacement levels (5% and 10%), although he did note small increases in air content, which can affect the consistency of the mix.",
    "Similarly, Samimi et al. [91] and Jokar et al.",
    "[92] reported a reduction in workability by 10-35% as the amount of zeolite increased, highlighting that natural zeolite can impact the fluidity and adhesiveness of concrete, especially at higher replacement levels.",
    "From the data presented in Table 9, it is evident that there are various effects from using Zeolite on fresh, mechanical, and durability properties.",
    "Nandhini and Karthikeyan [93], Maqsood and Eddie [94] found that adding eggshell powder in various forms pulverized (PES), treated (TESP), and calcined (CESP) generally reduces the workability of concrete."
  ]
